article.headline: E. Kentucky 42, Tennessee Tech 29
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. -- T.J. Pryor passed for four touchdowns and ran for another Saturday, leading Eastern Kentucky to a 42-29 win over Tennessee Tech. Orlandus Harris and Tyrone Goard caught two touchdowns each from Pryor, who completed 14 of 24 passes for 279 yards. Harris, who had nine receptions for 200 yards, scored on 13- and 55-yard pass plays. Goard's touchdowns came on 39- and 5-yard catches. Pryor, who rushed for 100 yards on 18 carries, also scored on a 37-yard run for the Colonels (5-5, 4-2 Ohio Valley Conference). H.B. Banjoman also scored on a 34-yard run and finished with 103 yards on 13 carries. Cass Barnes ran for a touchdown and threw a 19-yard scoring pass to Tim Benford for the Golden Eagles (4-6, 3-4), who were penalized 13 times for 90 yards. Barnes completed 18 of 30 passes for 273 yards, and Benford had six catches for 99 yards.
